This paper discusses the limitations of neural network architectures in terms of their ability to approximate functions, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the topological constraints imposed by the architecture, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity needed to approximate functions, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
